# AI Interview Agent Backend Architecture Rules

You are working on the AI Interview Agent backend.

IMPORTANT:
Before making ANY backend changes, ALWAYS review and understand the architecture defined in these core files first.

Never modify backend code based only on the current file. Always cross-check against the architecture source of truth.

---

# Architecture Source of Truth (MUST READ)

## Main Architecture Documents

1. ARCHITECTURE_README.md
2. ARCHITECTURE_REFACTOR_COMPLETE.md

These documents define:
- Overall system architecture
- Layer responsibilities
- Data flow
- Migration status
- API design
- LangGraph workflow design
- RAG integration rules
- Future extension rules

---

# Core Backend Files (ALWAYS CHECK)

## API Layer

Location:

app/api/interview_agent.py

Purpose:
- REST API endpoints only
- Request validation
- Response formatting
- Error handling
- Calling orchestrator

Rules:
- API MUST NOT contain business logic
- API MUST NOT call database directly
- API MUST NOT call LLM directly
- API MUST NOT generate questions
- API MUST NOT evaluate answers

Flow:

Frontend
    ↓
API Router
    ↓
InterviewOrchestrator
    ↓
LangGraph Workflow
    ↓
Agents
    ↓
Repositories / Services


---

# Orchestrator Layer

Location:

app/orchestrators/

Main file:

app/orchestrators/interview_orchestrator.py


Purpose:
- Coordinate API requests
- Prepare LangGraph state
- Load session information
- Execute workflows
- Return results

Rules:
- Orchestrator coordinates ONLY
- Business intelligence belongs inside agents
- Database access only through repositories
- Do not put prompts here
- Do not put LLM logic here


---

# LangGraph Layer

Location:

app/graph/


Files:

app/graph/interview_state.py

Defines the shared state object.

Before changing workflow logic:
ALWAYS inspect InterviewState first.


app/graph/interview_workflow.py

Main workflow definition.


app/graph/question_workflow.py

Question generation workflow.


app/graph/evaluation_workflow.py

Answer evaluation workflow.


Rules:

LangGraph controls:
- State transitions
- Node execution
- Conditional routing
- Interview flow


Never bypass LangGraph by directly calling agents.


---

# Agent Layer

Location:

app/agents/


## session_init_node.py

Responsible for:
- Initializing interview state


## company_context_node.py

Responsible for:
- Company RAG retrieval
- Pinecone namespace handling
- Injecting company context


IMPORTANT:

Every company interview MUST maintain:

company_id
        ↓
Pinecone namespace:
company_{company_id}
        ↓
Retriever
        ↓
Company documents
        ↓
Question generation context


Never generate company interview questions without checking company context.


## question_generation_node.py

Responsible for:
- AI generated interview questions

Rules:
- NO hardcoded questions
- NO templates
- ALWAYS use LLM
- Use:
  - company context
  - job role
  - candidate profile
  - conversation history
  - difficulty


## answer_evaluator_node.py

Responsible for:
- Answer evaluation
- Scoring
- Feedback generation


Rules:
- Use LLM evaluator
- Return structured evaluation
- Do not mix question generation logic


## decision_node.py

Responsible for:
- Adaptive interview decisions

Controls:
- difficulty changes
- phase transitions
- next action


---

# Repository Layer

Location:

app/repositories/


Purpose:

Database abstraction only.

Rules:

Allowed:
- CRUD operations
- Queries
- Database transactions


Forbidden:
- LLM calls
- Business decisions
- Prompt handling


All database access MUST go through repositories.


---

# Service Layer

Location:

app/services/


Important files:

## llm_service.py

Central LLM gateway.

Rules:
All LLM calls MUST use this service.

Never:

```python
llm.invoke(...)